From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 30 Jan 2026 19:28:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] ==== biggest_system_ram fixup ====

mm/damon: fixup ram walks and better support addr_unit on modules

DAMON physical address space operation set, DAMON_RECALIM and
DAMON_LRU_SORT sets the biggest system ram as the default access
monitoring target.  The function for walking the system ram resources
and finding the biggest one, namely damon_find_biggest_system_ram() has
below two issues.

First, it is mistakenly assigning end addresses of fully-closed ranges
to end addresses of open-ended ranges.  Second, it is assigning
'resource_size_t' value to 'unsigned long'.

None of the above causes a real user issue.  Please read descriptions of
the individual patches of this series to see why they are safe.  But
those are making the code bit difficult to read.

Fix the issues.  Fixing the second issue makes supporting LPAE like
environment on DAMON_RECLAIM and DAMON_LRU_SORT for the default
monitoring target quite easy.  Add the support together.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260131015643.79158-1-sj@kernel.org

